news.title: Weaver Services to raise ₹1,482 crore from Lightspeed, Premji Invest
news.para: Weaver Services, a tech-led housing finance platform, is raising Rs 1,481.5 crore in funding led by Lightspeed and Premji Invest. Focused on affordable housing, Weaver targets self-employed individuals in smaller cities. The funds will support asset acquisitions, tech development, and expansion. Weaver uses AI to improve loan approvals and credit assessment.

news.title: Housing finance companies struggle as mortgage rate war intensifies
news.para: Housing finance companies are grappling with squeezed margins due to aggressive mortgage rate pricing by public sector banks. Despite increased loan disbursals, AUM growth remains sluggish as borrowers switch to competitors offering lower rates. This intense competition and rate war are expected to persist, impacting even major players like LIC Housing Finance and Bajaj Housing Finance.

news.title: Jaipur development body goes online with lease process
news.para: The Jaipur Development Authority (JDA) has fully digitized its lease and lease deed issuance process, eliminating the need for in-person visits. Citizens can now complete the entire procedure online, from application to lease issuance, with Aadhaar-based e-KYC and digital signatures.

news.title: Over 7.5 acres in heart of Hyderabad to be auctioned today; ₹500 crore expected from sale
news.para: The Telangana Housing Board is set to auction over 7.5 acres of prime residential land in Kukatpally, expecting to generate ₹500 crore. Alongside, 618 unfinished 3BHK flats in Pocharam and Gajularamaram will also be auctioned. Funds raised will support affordable housing projects and the Indiramma housing scheme, building on recent successful auctions.

news.title: With FIRs, Noida authority plans crackdown on illegal constructions
news.para: Noida Authority is cracking down on illegal constructions by directing officials to file FIRs and pursue pending police cases. A consolidated database will monitor enforcement efforts, ensuring accountability and preventing delays. The Authority will also enhance public awareness with updated signage and focus on preventing encroachments in flood-prone areas, coordinating with various departments for effective action.

news.title: Housing finance companies under lens over lending faults
news.para: The National Housing Bank is intensifying its scrutiny of housing finance companies due to breaches in loan-to-value regulations, particularly for high-value home loans exceeding ₹75 lakh. Lenders are found to be disbursing loans up to 90% LTV, violating the stipulated 75% cap.

news.title: Prayagraj: 9,000 PMAY beneficiaries claim ₹1.2 lakh subsidy each by posing as homeless
news.para: A massive fraud has been uncovered in Prayagraj, where over 9,000 individuals falsely claimed housing subsidies under the Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana, despite already owning homes. Investigations also revealed pension fraud across various government schemes, resulting in a loss of Rs 40 lakh due to fake claims and unreported deaths.

news.title: Consumer forum holds Parsvanath Developers liable for delay in handing over flat
news.para: Parsvanath Developers Limited has been held liable by the Delhi State Consumer Disputes Redressal Commission for delaying possession of a residential flat booked in 2007. The commission directed the builder to hand over the flat and pay Rs 5.5 lakh in compensation to the complainants, Nitin and Amita Bansal, citing deficiency in service and unfair trade practices.

news.title: Assigned farmlands fuel illegal real estate deals around Hyderabad
news.para: Illegal sales of government-assigned lands are rampant around Hyderabad, particularly in Rangareddy, Medchal, and Vikarabad districts. Assignees are selling agricultural land to developers for quick profit, who then use it for real estate projects. Authorities are detecting violations and resuming land, with 24 acres reclaimed in Tukkuguda.

news.title: KVN Properties plans to raise ₹1,000 crore to expand business
news.para: KVN Properties, founded by former Prestige Estates CEO Venkat K Narayana, is reportedly in discussions with Kotak Realty Fund to raise Rs 1,000 crore through debentures. The capital will fuel expansion of its land portfolio across India, targeting 10 million sq ft of development potential by 2026.

news.title: CCI approves Phoenix Mills acquisition of CPP Investments' 49% stake in ISMDPL
news.para: The Competition Commission of India (CCI) has approved The Phoenix Mills' (PML) proposal to acquire Canada Pension Plan Investment Board's (CPP Investments) 49% stake in Island Star Mall Development (ISMDPL). PML will gain full ownership of ISMDPL for ₹5,449.16 crore.

news.title: EFC India to debut on NSE on August 20
news.para: EFC (I), an integrated office infrastructure firm, will debut on the NSE on August 20, anticipating improved liquidity and investor confidence. The company's Q1 FY26 net profit surged 196% to ₹46.7 crore, with operating income nearly doubling.

news.title: REA Group appoints Cameron McIntyre as new chief executive officer
news.para: Cameron McIntyre will become the CEO of REA Group. The appointment is effective from November 3, 2025. He succeeds Owen Wilson. Wilson is retiring from his full-time executive role. McIntyre was previously managing director and CEO of CAR Group. Wilson will transition to chair of REA India after his CEO tenure. He will ensure a smooth transition before stepping down.

news.title: UltraTech Cement eyes 200 MTPA capacity by FY26
news.para: UltraTech Cement aims to exceed 200 MTPA capacity by FY26, driven by strong FY25 performance with a 14% sales volume increase and significant capacity additions through acquisitions. The company reported robust Q1 FY26 results, including a 49% surge in profit after tax. UltraTech is also committed to sustainability, achieving one GW of renewable energy capacity and reducing CO₂ emissions.

news.title: Nagpur's new development plan in offing, 90% of old plan still on paper after 25 years
news.para: Nagpur is nearing the deadline for its new Development Plan (DP), facing skepticism due to past failures. The city received 43 suggestions, mainly from landowners seeking removal of long-standing property reservations from the 2000 DP. With a December 2025 deadline, the NMC aims to create a comprehensive plan, but challenges remain in incorporating all areas and addressing unresolved reservations.

news.title: India’s InvIT market to triple, touch $258 billion by 2030: Knight Frank
news.para: India's Infrastructure Investment Trusts (InvITs) are poised for substantial growth, projected to reach USD 258 billion in assets under management by 2030, driven by increased infrastructure spending and government initiatives like the National Monetisation Pipeline.

news.title: Construction costs surge 40% in five years, affordable housing share plummets to 12% in H1 2025: Anarock
news.para: India's affordable housing sector grapples with soaring construction costs, escalating nearly 40% since 2021, driven by inflation and supply chain issues. This surge has squeezed supply, with affordable housing launches plummeting from 40% in 2019 to just 12% in H1 2025. Potential tariffs and rising labor costs further threaten affordability, though GST reforms offer slight relief.

news.title: House of Abhinandan Lodha partners with Zepto to market housing plots
news.para: House of Abhinandan Lodha (HoABL) has partnered with Zepto to market its residential plots, starting with premium plots in Vrindavan and Neral. This collaboration expands HoABL's reach by allowing customers to discover and engage with their offerings on the Zepto app. Prospective customers can connect with an HOABL expert within 10 minutes for guidance via video call.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh forms panel to unlock land hurdles for industry
news.para: The Uttar Pradesh government has formed a high-level committee to optimize land utilization across Noida, Greater Noida, and Yamuna Expressway authorities. This decision addresses significant gaps between notified, master-planned, and acquired land, hindering industrial development. The committee will recommend strategies to accelerate land acquisition, streamline approvals, and unlock land parcels for industrial use, aligning with the state's investment promotion policy.

news.title: LML Realty to invest ₹150 crore to develop industrial park in Haryana
news.para: LML Realty is set to invest ₹150 crore in developing its inaugural industrial park in Firozpur Jhirka, Haryana, approved under the PADMA scheme. Spanning 35 acres, the park will feature ready-to-move units and various facilities. MSMEs establishing operations there will benefit from incentives like SGST refunds and capital subsidies.
